USA: Sun cuts U.S. posted crude prices 50 cts.Sun cuts U.S. posted crude prices 50 cts.Sun Co Inc it cut the price it will pay for U.S. crude oil by 50 cents a barrel, effective today.The decrease brings the new price for U.S. benchmark grade West Texas Intermediate to $21.25 a barrel, and West Texas Sour to $18.75 a barrel.Light Louisiana sweet crude is now $21.00 a barrel, and Oklahoma sweet is $21.25.-- New York Energy Desk, +1 212 859-1620